shanghai has been a  political  hub of china since the  20th century  many of chinas top government officials in beijing are known to have risen in shanghai in the 1980s on a platform that was critical of the extreme leftism of the  cultural revolution  giving them the tag  shanghai clique  during the 1990s  many observers of chinese politics view the more rightleaning shanghai clique as an opposing and competing faction of the current chinese administration under president  hu jintao  and premier  wen jiabao  shanghais top jobs the party chief and the position of mayor have always been prominent on a national scale four shanghai mayors eventually went on to take prominent central government positions including former president  jiang zemin  and former premier  zhu rongji  the top administrative jobs are always appointed directly by the central government
